latestIgtvVideos.title: Youtube Trailer🙈
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I'm all emo rn-  it's going to be a long caption.
I have always been fairly good at art- I didn't take it very seriously until a few years ago when I was pursuing my graduation and Xavier's has a fest every now and then. I would see people in the quad painting large large sheets and wished I could do it too. Fun fact, I didn't interview for it but what I did was- start painting and selling my art.
After graduation, I joined a company as a full time employee and I would keep getting painting orders back in 2018- so I would juggle between my full time job and my part time painting business. Fast forward to 2020, I was fortunate enough to get a project from Little Italy for their cafe in Bangalore and this project gave me a little confidence- I'm not bragging here but I was kind of proud because I always wanted to do something like this and tbh, I never thought I'd work at a company although I did my graduation in IT. Everyone who comes home- thinks I've done an art course - well, I haven't. Okay, I got a little carried away but back to this video - I always wanted to do YouTube. If you know me- I'm sure I've mentioned it at least once. I wasn't very sure if I'll be able to do it- I'm still not but I'm ready to take a shot at it. It would mean the world to me if you subscribe to my channel and help me pursue this long lost dream. I've put the link in my bio. The video will be up tomorrow at 4pm IST- It's not the best but it's good for a start and I'm sure you'll enjoy it. :)

Love❤️

latestIgtvVideos.title: Maa❤️
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
I wasn't going to put this up. This was supposed to be only for my mom to see. It's not my best work. It's a mess. You'll spot a lot of mistakes if you pay attention but I just want to be real here. I have days where I am so disappointed with my work. I thought this wasn't instagram worthy and only when @yellow.submarine.10 saw this and asked me to put it up, I realised it was never for the number of views or likes. It was supposed to convey an emotion we all feel deeply. Please watch it and show it to your mumma? I know it's late but I mean does it really matter what time or day it is? Let's celebrate motherhood every day and give them just as much love we give them on this day, every day. ❤️
.
